<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">357.116 M 82/1: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-09T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 9,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>14. Department’s circular April 5, 1 p.m.<note n="34" xml:id="d197fn34">See footnote 30, <ref target="#pg_248">p. 248</ref>.</note> Your
                            No. 11, April 9, 3 p.m. Mormon case.</p>
                        <p>Request careful reconsideration of matter, and ask no drastic action be
                            taken until case can be fully investigated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>